Thanks! I like the example. Though that's a new expression of the minimum runtime that I've never seen before. Usually in the literature the adiabatic condition is given by $\tau \gg 
    \frac{\underset{0\leq s \leq 1}{\text{max}}
    \left|\langle\psi_1(s)|
    \dfrac{d \hat{\mathscr{H}}(s)}
    {d s}|\psi_0(s)\rangle\right|}
    {\underset{0\leq s \leq 1}{\text{min}}\Delta^2(s)};
    \qquad s\equiv\frac{t}{\tau}$
where $\Delta^2(s) = (E_1(s)-E_0(s))^2$. See Ref [[1](https://arxiv.org/abs/0801.2193v3)] & [[2](https://journals.aps.org/prl/abstract/10.1103/PhysRevLett.102.220401)]

